# bottega runtime scratch (per-target): the registry JSON, the .bottega/wt/<id>
# worktrees, and the SHA-256-verified APS binaries in .bottega/bin/ are all run-time
# state, never committed. The APS lockfile (.bottega/aps.lock) IS committed — so
# ignore the directory's contents and re-include the lock (a whole-dir `.bottega/`
# ignore can't re-include a child). Matches the target gitignore the coordinator
# writes at run time (config.yaml + slice-wavefront).
.bottega/*
!.bottega/aps.lock
